description.narrative: Inter-ministerial engagement on issues concerning children affected by migration continued under the UNICEF-EU Protection of children affected by migration programme through the expanded Project Advisory Committee. Key achievements include progress in establishing a children's activity center in Kota Kinabalu with JKM, and the partnership with Child Frontiers to strengthen Social Welfare Services, including attention to alternative care for children affected by migration. An important partnership with SUHAKAM was also strengthened through a workplan that will include capacity building. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
